<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-11-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-11-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="1193" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1193">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/6966.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">San Luis Potosi</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-24">
                                    <hi rend="italic">3d November 24, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s November 22. Los Mochis matter taken up with Foreign
                            Secretary on train prior to arrival here. He said additional telegraphic
                            instruction for proper protection would be sent from San Luis
                            Potosi.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>